WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.446 align:middle line:90%


00:00:01.446 --> 00:00:03.374 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.374 --> 00:00:10.140 align:middle line:90%


00:00:10.140 --> 00:00:13.640 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA GARR: Hi, I'm Lisa Garr,
host of "Gaiam Inspirations."

00:00:13.640 --> 00:00:16.149 align:middle line:84%
Have you ever struggled
with addiction,

00:00:16.149 --> 00:00:18.570 align:middle line:84%
the kind that gets
a hold of you,

00:00:18.570 --> 00:00:21.210 align:middle line:84%
and then you're in
maybe denial of the fact

00:00:21.210 --> 00:00:23.420 align:middle line:90%
that it's gotten a hold of you?

00:00:23.420 --> 00:00:25.790 align:middle line:84%
Or are you just maybe
a social drinker

00:00:25.790 --> 00:00:28.750 align:middle line:84%
that drinks maybe
seven nights a week?

00:00:28.750 --> 00:00:33.080 align:middle line:84%
And that leads to more and
more drinking or drug use?

00:00:33.080 --> 00:00:34.780 align:middle line:90%
Well, joining me is Tommy Rosen.

00:00:34.780 --> 00:00:38.210 align:middle line:84%
He's an internationally
recognized yoga teacher

00:00:38.210 --> 00:00:41.000 align:middle line:84%
and addiction and
recovery expert.

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:44.470 align:middle line:84%
He has spent the last
two decades immersed

00:00:44.470 --> 00:00:49.380 align:middle line:84%
in yoga, recovery, and wellness,
which is very important.

00:00:49.380 --> 00:00:53.060 align:middle line:84%
He holds advanced certifications
in both hatha and kundalini

00:00:53.060 --> 00:00:56.720 align:middle line:84%
yoga, and he has more
than 23 years of recovery

00:00:56.720 --> 00:00:58.172 align:middle line:90%
from acute drug addiction.

00:00:58.172 --> 00:00:59.630 align:middle line:84%
And I'm so glad
you're here, Tommy,

00:00:59.630 --> 00:01:00.950 align:middle line:90%
thank you for joining me.

00:01:00.950 --> 00:01:01.460 align:middle line:90%
>>TOMMY ROSEN: Thank you, Lisa.

00:01:01.460 --> 00:01:02.820 align:middle line:90%
It is great to be with you.

00:01:02.820 --> 00:01:03.770 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I am so happy.

00:01:03.770 --> 00:01:08.450 align:middle line:84%
Now, you have combined these
two worlds of yoga and recovery

00:01:08.450 --> 00:01:09.390 align:middle line:90%
together.

00:01:09.390 --> 00:01:11.869 align:middle line:84%
Why did you put
those two together?

00:01:11.869 --> 00:01:13.410 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: I like to
say that necessity

00:01:13.410 --> 00:01:17.690 align:middle line:84%
is the mother of
invention, you know?

00:01:17.690 --> 00:01:23.900 align:middle line:84%
In our world today, when people
move, say, through addiction,

00:01:23.900 --> 00:01:26.019 align:middle line:84%
and they're finding
out, I have a problem,

00:01:26.019 --> 00:01:28.560 align:middle line:84%
and hopefully they've reached
a point where they can actually

00:01:28.560 --> 00:01:31.960 align:middle line:84%
say, I have a problem, this
thing is bigger than me,

00:01:31.960 --> 00:01:34.300 align:middle line:84%
there's a couple of
directions that someone

00:01:34.300 --> 00:01:35.950 align:middle line:90%
could take to get better.

00:01:35.950 --> 00:01:39.620 align:middle line:84%
One of the directions is
to enter a 12 step program.

00:01:39.620 --> 00:01:41.650 align:middle line:84%
Another direction
is to have some form

00:01:41.650 --> 00:01:43.980 align:middle line:84%
of therapeutic process
going on, a one

00:01:43.980 --> 00:01:46.210 align:middle line:90%
on one process with a therapist.

00:01:46.210 --> 00:01:47.780 align:middle line:90%
Different modalities.

00:01:47.780 --> 00:01:51.790 align:middle line:84%
Another is to enter
in-patient treatment,

00:01:51.790 --> 00:01:53.910 align:middle line:90%
or to have outpatient treatment.

00:01:53.910 --> 00:01:57.190 align:middle line:84%
And though all of those
systems are really

00:01:57.190 --> 00:02:00.580 align:middle line:84%
built to help you out
of chronic addiction,

00:02:00.580 --> 00:02:03.010 align:middle line:84%
to help you move from, OK,
I'm somebody that's stuck.

00:02:03.010 --> 00:02:06.050 align:middle line:84%
I have this issue, whether
that's drugs, alcohol, food,

00:02:06.050 --> 00:02:07.437 align:middle line:90%
sex, relationships, money--

00:02:07.437 --> 00:02:08.770 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Gambling, whatever, yes.

00:02:08.770 --> 00:02:10.580 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: Gambling,
the whole deal.

00:02:10.580 --> 00:02:13.110 align:middle line:84%
We'll help you to
move down a path where

00:02:13.110 --> 00:02:15.340 align:middle line:84%
you can get out of
chronic addiction.

00:02:15.340 --> 00:02:16.910 align:middle line:84%
Once you're out of
chronic addiction,

00:02:16.910 --> 00:02:19.230 align:middle line:84%
now you have a foundation,
which is wonderful.

00:02:19.230 --> 00:02:21.140 align:middle line:90%
And a miracle has taken place.

00:02:21.140 --> 00:02:22.980 align:middle line:90%
You've gotten out of addiction.

00:02:22.980 --> 00:02:26.410 align:middle line:84%
But now, you're back to
facing all of the things

00:02:26.410 --> 00:02:28.500 align:middle line:84%
about yourself that
you may have turned

00:02:28.500 --> 00:02:30.770 align:middle line:84%
to addictive behavior in
the first place to avoid.

00:02:30.770 --> 00:02:32.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I see, I see, yes.

00:02:32.480 --> 00:02:34.200 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: So now,
the question really

00:02:34.200 --> 00:02:36.800 align:middle line:84%
that happens for most of
us in recovery is now what?

00:02:36.800 --> 00:02:38.130 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You need a practice.

00:02:38.130 --> 00:02:41.140 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: Some kind of practice
that brings the body into it.

00:02:41.140 --> 00:02:44.820 align:middle line:84%
We learn-- most of us learn the
hard way-- I certainly learned

00:02:44.820 --> 00:02:49.330 align:middle line:84%
the hard way-- that there is a
deeper level of detoxification

00:02:49.330 --> 00:02:53.360 align:middle line:84%
which is necessary in the
body to be completely at ease

00:02:53.360 --> 00:02:58.610 align:middle line:84%
and to move forward in your life
and to be able to really start

00:02:58.610 --> 00:03:01.740 align:middle line:84%
to unravel the
traumas of your life.

00:03:01.740 --> 00:03:04.140 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Physical and
mental detoxification.

00:03:04.140 --> 00:03:05.047 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSEN: Absolutely.

00:03:05.047 --> 00:03:07.380 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Can you back us up a
little bit into your story?

00:03:07.380 --> 00:03:10.030 align:middle line:84%
How did you discover
in the first place

00:03:10.030 --> 00:03:13.720 align:middle line:84%
that you were in that
place of serious addiction?

00:03:13.720 --> 00:03:16.400 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: Originally,
well, it certainly

00:03:16.400 --> 00:03:20.130 align:middle line:84%
wasn't hard to see,
for most people.

00:03:20.130 --> 00:03:23.710 align:middle line:84%
I came, as most people
do, I had this perspective

00:03:23.710 --> 00:03:27.260 align:middle line:90%
that I know I'm in trouble.

00:03:27.260 --> 00:03:29.510 align:middle line:84%
Like, I even knew
I'm in trouble here.

00:03:29.510 --> 00:03:32.420 align:middle line:84%
But I'd always been
able to right the ship.

00:03:32.420 --> 00:03:35.430 align:middle line:84%
So that was-- the
basis of my denial

00:03:35.430 --> 00:03:39.220 align:middle line:84%
was I've always been able
to get through it before.

00:03:39.220 --> 00:03:41.520 align:middle line:84%
I'll figure out a way
to get through it again.

00:03:41.520 --> 00:03:43.720 align:middle line:90%
But that moment never came.

00:03:43.720 --> 00:03:45.400 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you
would always maybe

00:03:45.400 --> 00:03:47.030 align:middle line:84%
get clean and sober
for a little while,

00:03:47.030 --> 00:03:48.488 align:middle line:84%
and you'd be OK
for a little while?

00:03:48.488 --> 00:03:51.570 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: It wouldn't be
anything so clear as that.

00:03:51.570 --> 00:03:55.630 align:middle line:84%
It would be-- I'd be
partying for a run, taking

00:03:55.630 --> 00:03:57.880 align:middle line:84%
a lot of drugs and
alcohol, drinking,

00:03:57.880 --> 00:03:59.400 align:middle line:90%
partying, the whole thing.

00:03:59.400 --> 00:04:01.595 align:middle line:84%
And then there'd be--
I'd realize, wow,

00:04:01.595 --> 00:04:02.470 align:middle line:90%
this has got to stop.

00:04:02.470 --> 00:04:04.490 align:middle line:84%
And I'd put it on
hold for a week.

00:04:04.490 --> 00:04:08.380 align:middle line:84%
Put it on hold for a couple
weeks, not get clean and sober,

00:04:08.380 --> 00:04:09.149 align:middle line:90%
nothing like that.

00:04:09.149 --> 00:04:09.940 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, I see.

00:04:09.940 --> 00:04:11.930 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: This was
back originally.

00:04:11.930 --> 00:04:13.740 align:middle line:84%
Finally, what happened
for me is what

00:04:13.740 --> 00:04:17.600 align:middle line:84%
happens for a lot of people is I
reached what's called a bottom.

00:04:17.600 --> 00:04:19.690 align:middle line:84%
And I now know that
a bottom really

00:04:19.690 --> 00:04:22.675 align:middle line:84%
is just the moment when you're
ready to tell the truth.

00:04:22.675 --> 00:04:24.280 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Oh, it's
just the beginning.

00:04:24.280 --> 00:04:25.738 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: It's just
that moment that

00:04:25.738 --> 00:04:28.000 align:middle line:90%
happens where you're like, OK.

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:29.680 align:middle line:90%
This thing is bigger than me.

00:04:29.680 --> 00:04:31.110 align:middle line:90%
I can't do this.

00:04:31.110 --> 00:04:33.380 align:middle line:84%
I can't go on living
like I'm living,

00:04:33.380 --> 00:04:35.207 align:middle line:84%
but I have no idea
how else to live.

00:04:35.207 --> 00:04:36.040 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: How to stop.

00:04:36.040 --> 00:04:37.860 align:middle line:90%
So it's not a stop.

00:04:37.860 --> 00:04:40.236 align:middle line:84%
It's an oh my god, I need to
stop, but I'm out of control

00:04:40.236 --> 00:04:41.026 align:middle line:90%
and don't know how.

00:04:41.026 --> 00:04:42.100 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSEN: That's right.

00:04:42.100 --> 00:04:45.000 align:middle line:84%
And you pray at that
moment that somebody

00:04:45.000 --> 00:04:47.394 align:middle line:84%
is there to help guide
you towards some help.

00:04:47.394 --> 00:04:48.810 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Was someone
there for you?

00:04:48.810 --> 00:04:50.018 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSEN: My family was there.

00:04:50.018 --> 00:04:51.430 align:middle line:90%
My whole family was there.

00:04:51.430 --> 00:04:55.080 align:middle line:84%
Thank god they had
not abandoned me

00:04:55.080 --> 00:04:57.990 align:middle line:84%
through all of my
shenanigans all these years.

00:04:57.990 --> 00:05:00.456 align:middle line:84%
And they helped me
to get treatment.

00:05:00.456 --> 00:05:01.830 align:middle line:84%
And I went off to
Hazelton, which

00:05:01.830 --> 00:05:05.600 align:middle line:84%
is a really wonderful treatment
center up in Minnesota.

00:05:05.600 --> 00:05:06.100 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:05:06.100 --> 00:05:09.280 align:middle line:84%
And did you-- Now, you were
in your 20s at the time?

00:05:09.280 --> 00:05:10.656 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSEN: I was 22.

00:05:10.656 --> 00:05:12.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And out of college?

00:05:12.480 --> 00:05:13.570 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSEN: Young man.

00:05:13.570 --> 00:05:17.100 align:middle line:84%
I was a senior in college
when I left to go to rehab.

00:05:17.100 --> 00:05:17.910 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Hm.

00:05:17.910 --> 00:05:21.970 align:middle line:84%
So a ton of potential, but you
didn't-- so where do you think,

00:05:21.970 --> 00:05:24.710 align:middle line:90%
looking back now, that got lost?

00:05:24.710 --> 00:05:27.420 align:middle line:90%
That potential got misdirected?

00:05:27.420 --> 00:05:29.380 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: And that's a
great question, Lisa,

00:05:29.380 --> 00:05:32.660 align:middle line:84%
because what you'll hear about
most addicts and alcoholics is

00:05:32.660 --> 00:05:34.910 align:middle line:84%
people will tell them their
whole childhood, my god,

00:05:34.910 --> 00:05:36.530 align:middle line:90%
you have so much potential!

00:05:36.530 --> 00:05:37.900 align:middle line:90%
You have so much potential!

00:05:37.900 --> 00:05:39.775 align:middle line:84%
How come you're not
realizing your potential?

00:05:39.775 --> 00:05:42.066 align:middle line:84%
And then later on, when you're
doing drugs and alcohol,

00:05:42.066 --> 00:05:43.115 align:middle line:90%
why don't you just stop?

00:05:43.115 --> 00:05:45.590 align:middle line:90%
Why can't you just stop?

00:05:45.590 --> 00:05:50.160 align:middle line:84%
That potential that so
many alcoholics and addicts

00:05:50.160 --> 00:05:53.670 align:middle line:84%
have hopefully gets realized
later on in recovery.

00:05:53.670 --> 00:05:58.120 align:middle line:84%
For me, it began really
when I was 13 years old.

00:05:58.120 --> 00:06:01.160 align:middle line:84%
And the discomfort
of my childhood

00:06:01.160 --> 00:06:04.600 align:middle line:84%
coupled with an atrocious
diet and no sense

00:06:04.600 --> 00:06:08.870 align:middle line:84%
of how to sit still or to manage
stress, a lot of emotional pain

00:06:08.870 --> 00:06:11.690 align:middle line:84%
in my relationships at
home, a lot of struggles.

00:06:11.690 --> 00:06:14.200 align:middle line:84%
It all culminated in just
a level of discomfort

00:06:14.200 --> 00:06:17.080 align:middle line:84%
that I was absolutely
unwilling to face.

00:06:17.080 --> 00:06:19.690 align:middle line:84%
So when I found,
actually, marijuana--

00:06:19.690 --> 00:06:22.010 align:middle line:84%
when I found marijuana,
it was at the time

00:06:22.010 --> 00:06:24.470 align:middle line:90%
the greatest find of my life.

00:06:24.470 --> 00:06:25.662 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It relaxed you?

00:06:25.662 --> 00:06:27.120 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: First
time, I felt like it

00:06:27.120 --> 00:06:29.500 align:middle line:84%
was the first deep breath I
had taken in my life ever.

00:06:29.500 --> 00:06:30.320 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:06:30.320 --> 00:06:34.200 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: And it was Nancy
Reagan and Ronald Reagan,

00:06:34.200 --> 00:06:36.510 align:middle line:84%
they were in power
in the United States.

00:06:36.510 --> 00:06:40.870 align:middle line:84%
And Nancy had her
Just Say No campaign.

00:06:40.870 --> 00:06:43.910 align:middle line:84%
It just didn't quite cover
the problem for me, you know?

00:06:43.910 --> 00:06:46.270 align:middle line:90%
Just say no wasn't working.

00:06:46.270 --> 00:06:48.739 align:middle line:90%
So I just went down this road.

00:06:48.739 --> 00:06:50.530 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Did you ever
hear that in recovery?

00:06:50.530 --> 00:06:52.590 align:middle line:90%
Just say no!

00:06:52.590 --> 00:06:53.980 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSEN: Well, it's so absurd.

00:06:53.980 --> 00:06:55.390 align:middle line:84%
It's like walking up
to a homeless person.

00:06:55.390 --> 00:06:56.639 align:middle line:90%
Why don't you just get a home?

00:06:56.639 --> 00:06:57.970 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right, right.

00:06:57.970 --> 00:07:00.400 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: It's not taking the
full picture into account.

00:07:00.400 --> 00:07:01.260 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:07:01.260 --> 00:07:04.200 align:middle line:84%
It's easy to say, but
harder and harder to do.

00:07:04.200 --> 00:07:08.620 align:middle line:84%
So when you found recovery, and
then you got out of recovery,

00:07:08.620 --> 00:07:10.480 align:middle line:90%
how did you find yoga?

00:07:10.480 --> 00:07:13.750 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: OK, so
my story is really

00:07:13.750 --> 00:07:16.440 align:middle line:84%
a story of recovery
within recovery.

00:07:16.440 --> 00:07:21.400 align:middle line:84%
Now, my first year
of recovery was 1991.

00:07:21.400 --> 00:07:23.350 align:middle line:90%
I went to rehab in '89.

00:07:23.350 --> 00:07:25.790 align:middle line:90%
I stayed sober for a year.

00:07:25.790 --> 00:07:27.710 align:middle line:90%
I relapsed for a whole year.

00:07:27.710 --> 00:07:31.050 align:middle line:84%
In, out, in, out, in, out, can't
stay sober, can't stay sober.

00:07:31.050 --> 00:07:34.640 align:middle line:84%
At the end of that
year, June 23, 1991,

00:07:34.640 --> 00:07:37.340 align:middle line:84%
was the last time I
had a drug or a drink.

00:07:37.340 --> 00:07:40.240 align:middle line:84%
That year, I was
in San Francisco.

00:07:40.240 --> 00:07:44.147 align:middle line:84%
And there was this
big sign, yoga!

00:07:44.147 --> 00:07:46.480 align:middle line:84%
I had heard about yoga, and
I'd been interested in yoga,

00:07:46.480 --> 00:07:48.410 align:middle line:84%
but I'd certainly
never ventured--

00:07:48.410 --> 00:07:51.580 align:middle line:84%
I literally walked off the
street into a yoga class.

00:07:51.580 --> 00:07:53.300 align:middle line:84%
The teacher's name
was Janet McCloud.

00:07:53.300 --> 00:07:55.160 align:middle line:90%
She's still a teacher today.

00:07:55.160 --> 00:07:56.500 align:middle line:90%
And I walked into her class.

00:07:56.500 --> 00:07:58.797 align:middle line:84%
And a couple things were
remarkable about this class

00:07:58.797 --> 00:07:59.380 align:middle line:90%
and about her.

00:07:59.380 --> 00:08:02.690 align:middle line:84%
Number one, she moved with
so much elegance and grace

00:08:02.690 --> 00:08:04.200 align:middle line:90%
that I couldn't believe it.

00:08:04.200 --> 00:08:06.730 align:middle line:84%
I literally thought I
was looking at a cartoon.

00:08:06.730 --> 00:08:09.970 align:middle line:84%
And she would bend or
get into a yoga pose.

00:08:09.970 --> 00:08:11.520 align:middle line:84%
And she'd move to
the point that you

00:08:11.520 --> 00:08:13.577 align:middle line:84%
thought a normal human
being should move to.

00:08:13.577 --> 00:08:14.910 align:middle line:90%
And then, she'd just keep going.

00:08:14.910 --> 00:08:15.175 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Beyond?

00:08:15.175 --> 00:08:15.980 align:middle line:90%
Wow.

00:08:15.980 --> 00:08:18.650 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: And I was like,
this doesn't look correct.

00:08:18.650 --> 00:08:21.800 align:middle line:84%
The feeling that I had was
she had so much freedom

00:08:21.800 --> 00:08:25.770 align:middle line:84%
in her body, it was an
outward representation

00:08:25.770 --> 00:08:27.532 align:middle line:84%
of what I had always
been looking for.

00:08:27.532 --> 00:08:28.740 align:middle line:90%
I'd been looking for freedom.

00:08:28.740 --> 00:08:30.031 align:middle line:90%
I'd been looking for a way out.

00:08:30.031 --> 00:08:32.580 align:middle line:84%
How do I transcend the
problems of my life?

00:08:32.580 --> 00:08:34.950 align:middle line:84%
How do I move
beyond things that I

00:08:34.950 --> 00:08:37.360 align:middle line:90%
don't know how to move beyond?

00:08:37.360 --> 00:08:41.320 align:middle line:84%
In her body, the way that she
moved, her elegance, her grace,

00:08:41.320 --> 00:08:42.950 align:middle line:90%
it was that.

00:08:42.950 --> 00:08:45.620 align:middle line:90%
And I wanted it so badly.

00:08:45.620 --> 00:08:48.620 align:middle line:84%
And I had a
relationship with yoga

00:08:48.620 --> 00:08:51.140 align:middle line:84%
for the next-- I've had
a relationship with yoga

00:08:51.140 --> 00:08:51.640 align:middle line:90%
since then.

00:08:51.640 --> 00:08:53.770 align:middle line:84%
But I had one kind
of relationship

00:08:53.770 --> 00:08:55.750 align:middle line:84%
with yoga through
the first 12 years

00:08:55.750 --> 00:08:59.380 align:middle line:84%
of my recovery, which was
very physically based.

00:08:59.380 --> 00:09:02.500 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't much about going
deeper or meditation.

00:09:02.500 --> 00:09:04.510 align:middle line:84%
It was just, let's
get a good workout.

00:09:04.510 --> 00:09:06.120 align:middle line:90%
Let's get a good sweat.

00:09:06.120 --> 00:09:07.927 align:middle line:90%
And let's breathe and move.

00:09:07.927 --> 00:09:08.635 align:middle line:90%
And that's great.

00:09:08.635 --> 00:09:09.776 align:middle line:90%
And that's wonderful.

00:09:09.776 --> 00:09:11.650 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And it started
to detoxify your body?

00:09:11.650 --> 00:09:15.580 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: Oh, no question,
I moved forward.

00:09:15.580 --> 00:09:18.220 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And did you clean up
your diet at the same time?

00:09:18.220 --> 00:09:20.202 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSEN: Not completely.

00:09:20.202 --> 00:09:21.160 align:middle line:90%
It took a little while.

00:09:21.160 --> 00:09:22.690 align:middle line:84%
My diet certainly
came a long way

00:09:22.690 --> 00:09:24.520 align:middle line:90%
from where I was as a child.

00:09:24.520 --> 00:09:25.270 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Which was?

00:09:25.270 --> 00:09:28.060 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: I hadn't had a salad
until I was 18 years old.

00:09:28.060 --> 00:09:28.990 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:09:28.990 --> 00:09:30.820 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: I didn't
eat vegetables.

00:09:30.820 --> 00:09:33.220 align:middle line:84%
I ate processed
food of every kind--

00:09:33.220 --> 00:09:37.030 align:middle line:90%
candy and Doritos and Coca-Cola.

00:09:37.030 --> 00:09:39.060 align:middle line:84%
I bounced through my
childhood from one sugar

00:09:39.060 --> 00:09:41.220 align:middle line:90%
event to the next, basically.

00:09:41.220 --> 00:09:43.360 align:middle line:84%
All the meat that
I ate was-- came

00:09:43.360 --> 00:09:46.030 align:middle line:84%
from animals that basically
lived horrible lives

00:09:46.030 --> 00:09:47.250 align:middle line:90%
and then were killed.

00:09:47.250 --> 00:09:48.200 align:middle line:90%
Nothing was organic.

00:09:48.200 --> 00:09:49.190 align:middle line:90%
Nothing was free range.

00:09:49.190 --> 00:09:52.190 align:middle line:90%
Everything was artificial.

00:09:52.190 --> 00:09:53.730 align:middle line:90%
I suffered around that diet.

00:09:53.730 --> 00:09:56.160 align:middle line:90%
I was sick so much as a child.

00:09:56.160 --> 00:09:59.030 align:middle line:84%
I set my body and my mind
up for a whopping case

00:09:59.030 --> 00:10:00.575 align:middle line:90%
of drug addiction later on.

00:10:00.575 --> 00:10:02.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Because of the
other chemicals in the food?

00:10:02.700 --> 00:10:03.820 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: Oh, the
chemicals in the food,

00:10:03.820 --> 00:10:05.560 align:middle line:84%
but just also that
you're making yourself

00:10:05.560 --> 00:10:07.314 align:middle line:90%
into a weaker human being.

00:10:07.314 --> 00:10:09.730 align:middle line:84%
And this is a point that I
like to talk to people about is

00:10:09.730 --> 00:10:14.330 align:middle line:84%
that I really see that addiction
is a opportunistic disease.

00:10:14.330 --> 00:10:16.760 align:middle line:84%
I believe it will take
advantage of weakness.

00:10:16.760 --> 00:10:19.360 align:middle line:84%
So part of recovery for me,
and this is the key part,

00:10:19.360 --> 00:10:22.550 align:middle line:84%
is you have to build yourself
into a strong person.

00:10:22.550 --> 00:10:24.880 align:middle line:84%
I don't mean just physically
strong, at every level.

00:10:24.880 --> 00:10:26.120 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's a great point.

00:10:26.120 --> 00:10:28.565 align:middle line:84%
So a weakened immune system
is a Petri dish for addiction.

00:10:28.565 --> 00:10:29.981 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: Oh yeah,
for any disease.

00:10:29.981 --> 00:10:31.370 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:10:31.370 --> 00:10:33.870 align:middle line:84%
Was there addiction
genetically in your family?

00:10:33.870 --> 00:10:35.940 align:middle line:84%
Or did that come
into play at all?

00:10:35.940 --> 00:10:38.290 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: The genetic
piece for me--

00:10:38.290 --> 00:10:40.000 align:middle line:90%
so I can look back at my family.

00:10:40.000 --> 00:10:43.250 align:middle line:84%
And I can tell you that
we've had a couple suicides

00:10:43.250 --> 00:10:45.750 align:middle line:84%
over the past three or
four generations, so

00:10:45.750 --> 00:10:48.590 align:middle line:90%
certainly depression.

00:10:48.590 --> 00:10:51.390 align:middle line:84%
Certainly my mother
struggled with alcoholism.

00:10:51.390 --> 00:10:54.120 align:middle line:90%
My grandfather struggled.

00:10:54.120 --> 00:10:56.840 align:middle line:84%
There's elements in
there, not everybody,

00:10:56.840 --> 00:10:59.750 align:middle line:84%
but there's elements
through there.

00:10:59.750 --> 00:11:03.062 align:middle line:84%
When I think about the
genetic question, genetics

00:11:03.062 --> 00:11:05.270 align:middle line:84%
most people are like, oh,
well I have these genetics.

00:11:05.270 --> 00:11:07.150 align:middle line:90%
What can I do about it?

00:11:07.150 --> 00:11:10.070 align:middle line:84%
Or I have a predisposition,
I better be very careful.

00:11:10.070 --> 00:11:12.810 align:middle line:84%
The fact is that the
science of epigenetics

00:11:12.810 --> 00:11:17.840 align:middle line:84%
is helping us understand that
our behavior, our attitude,

00:11:17.840 --> 00:11:20.610 align:middle line:84%
the people we hang out
with, the food that we eat,

00:11:20.610 --> 00:11:22.940 align:middle line:84%
the environments
we put ourselves in

00:11:22.940 --> 00:11:26.700 align:middle line:84%
are going to actually have an
effect on our genetic readout.

00:11:26.700 --> 00:11:29.030 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It turns on all
those genetic markers, right?

00:11:29.030 --> 00:11:31.400 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: Or doesn't allow
the bad ones to turn on.

00:11:31.400 --> 00:11:37.940 align:middle line:84%
So if that addiction
marker is not turned on,

00:11:37.940 --> 00:11:41.990 align:middle line:84%
you could have the
predisposition for alcoholism

00:11:41.990 --> 00:11:44.700 align:middle line:90%
but never become an alcoholic.

00:11:44.700 --> 00:11:46.840 align:middle line:84%
So it begs the question,
what's involved?

00:11:46.840 --> 00:11:47.410 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:11:47.410 --> 00:11:49.560 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSEN: So environment.

00:11:49.560 --> 00:11:52.970 align:middle line:84%
If I said to you,
Lisa, do you think

00:11:52.970 --> 00:11:55.960 align:middle line:84%
you would know how to
make-- how to nurture

00:11:55.960 --> 00:11:58.550 align:middle line:84%
and how to create a
healthy human being?

00:11:58.550 --> 00:12:01.500 align:middle line:84%
Somebody who felt a sense
of esteem for themself?

00:12:01.500 --> 00:12:06.980 align:middle line:84%
Somebody who felt good, who felt
confident, who felt healthy?

00:12:06.980 --> 00:12:08.480 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I've had
to learn all that.

00:12:08.480 --> 00:12:10.030 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSEN: Right, we all have.

00:12:10.030 --> 00:12:10.872 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:12:10.872 --> 00:12:12.330 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: But you
know how to do it.

00:12:12.330 --> 00:12:15.572 align:middle line:84%
And the same thing goes
for if I said to you, Lisa,

00:12:15.572 --> 00:12:17.280 align:middle line:84%
we're going to take
this child, and we're

00:12:17.280 --> 00:12:19.820 align:middle line:84%
going to make an addict
out of this child,

00:12:19.820 --> 00:12:21.920 align:middle line:90%
you'd know exactly what to do.

00:12:21.920 --> 00:12:23.920 align:middle line:90%
Treat them inconsistently.

00:12:23.920 --> 00:12:26.230 align:middle line:84%
Make them feel bad
about themselves.

00:12:26.230 --> 00:12:28.860 align:middle line:84%
Give them a really,
really addictive diet

00:12:28.860 --> 00:12:30.620 align:middle line:90%
based on a lot of sugar.

00:12:30.620 --> 00:12:34.180 align:middle line:84%
Make them feel insecure in who
they are and what they are.

00:12:34.180 --> 00:12:37.450 align:middle line:84%
And then, right when
they're coming of age,

00:12:37.450 --> 00:12:39.956 align:middle line:84%
introduce an
addictive substance.

00:12:39.956 --> 00:12:41.750 align:middle line:90%
And boom, it's done.

00:12:41.750 --> 00:12:43.720 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Like sugar,
like caffeine?

00:12:43.720 --> 00:12:47.169 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: Like
marijuana, alcohol, sex.

00:12:47.169 --> 00:12:47.960 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Well, food.

00:12:47.960 --> 00:12:48.960 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSEN: Food.

00:12:48.960 --> 00:12:52.527 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yeah, too much food,
and soothing emotions with food.

00:12:52.527 --> 00:12:53.360 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSEN: Absolutely.

00:12:53.360 --> 00:12:55.900 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's another huge--
it doesn't have to necessarily

00:12:55.900 --> 00:12:58.860 align:middle line:84%
be-- it could be a legal
substance, like food.

00:12:58.860 --> 00:13:05.200 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: Anything that you use
to help yourself to feel better

00:13:05.200 --> 00:13:09.279 align:middle line:84%
that causes-- creates
craving and ultimately brings

00:13:09.279 --> 00:13:10.820 align:middle line:84%
negative consequences
into your life.

00:13:10.820 --> 00:13:12.240 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: From the outside in.

00:13:12.240 --> 00:13:15.490 align:middle line:84%
So basically, the
antidote to setting up

00:13:15.490 --> 00:13:18.470 align:middle line:84%
the body for addiction is
to develop the strength

00:13:18.470 --> 00:13:19.860 align:middle line:90%
from the inside out.

00:13:19.860 --> 00:13:22.690 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: Absolutely,
along with connections,

00:13:22.690 --> 00:13:25.050 align:middle line:84%
healthy connections
with other human beings.

00:13:25.050 --> 00:13:26.730 align:middle line:90%
It turns out we need these.

00:13:26.730 --> 00:13:27.230 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes!

00:13:27.230 --> 00:13:28.661 align:middle line:90%
We do.

00:13:28.661 --> 00:13:31.530 align:middle line:90%
That's yes.

00:13:31.530 --> 00:13:33.550 align:middle line:84%
I know sometimes
I'm on the island.

00:13:33.550 --> 00:13:34.634 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSEN: Exactly, exactly.

00:13:34.634 --> 00:13:36.758 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But sometimes, you
have to go to the island

00:13:36.758 --> 00:13:38.800 align:middle line:84%
in order to know where
the other people are.

00:13:38.800 --> 00:13:40.258 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: Well,
there's a difference

00:13:40.258 --> 00:13:43.442 align:middle line:90%
between solitude and loneliness.

00:13:43.442 --> 00:13:44.650 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's a great point.

00:13:44.650 --> 00:13:46.980 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: Or solitude
and isolation.

00:13:46.980 --> 00:13:48.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So let's
talk about the mind.

00:13:48.800 --> 00:13:52.720 align:middle line:84%
You have a great video here
that talks about the ego

00:13:52.720 --> 00:13:55.330 align:middle line:90%
and how to eradicate the ego.

00:13:55.330 --> 00:13:56.350 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSEN: Ego eradicator.

00:13:56.350 --> 00:13:57.180 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ego eradicator.

00:13:57.180 --> 00:13:59.054 align:middle line:84%
I actually want to take
a look at this video.

00:13:59.054 --> 00:14:02.394 align:middle line:84%
Take a look with Tommy talking
about the ego eradicator.

00:14:02.394 --> 00:14:03.060 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:14:03.060 --> 00:14:05.100 align:middle line:90%
-What's up, daily love posse?

00:14:05.100 --> 00:14:06.050 align:middle line:90%
This is Tommy Rosen.

00:14:06.050 --> 00:14:08.430 align:middle line:84%
And this week's vlog
is all about what

00:14:08.430 --> 00:14:11.760 align:middle line:84%
you can do when your mind
becomes a bad neighborhood.

00:14:11.760 --> 00:14:14.570 align:middle line:84%
Most everybody can relate
to this idea of waking up

00:14:14.570 --> 00:14:17.780 align:middle line:84%
on the wrong side of the bed,
feeling like your mind has

00:14:17.780 --> 00:14:20.960 align:middle line:84%
control of you rather
than the other way around.

00:14:20.960 --> 00:14:23.820 align:middle line:84%
I feel like most people
have that experience

00:14:23.820 --> 00:14:25.330 align:middle line:90%
every single day.

00:14:25.330 --> 00:14:28.560 align:middle line:84%
What can we do to get
control of our mind?

00:14:28.560 --> 00:14:31.200 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to show you a
yoga exercise now called

00:14:31.200 --> 00:14:33.630 align:middle line:90%
ego eradicator.

00:14:33.630 --> 00:14:35.350 align:middle line:90%
It's three minutes in length.

00:14:35.350 --> 00:14:37.500 align:middle line:84%
You can extend it to
any length you'd like,

00:14:37.500 --> 00:14:38.770 align:middle line:90%
but three minutes will do it.

00:14:38.770 --> 00:14:40.080 align:middle line:90%
Trust me.

00:14:40.080 --> 00:14:42.180 align:middle line:84%
We'll do it together
and have this experience

00:14:42.180 --> 00:14:45.190 align:middle line:84%
of what it's like to gain
control over your mind

00:14:45.190 --> 00:14:47.490 align:middle line:84%
and to be able to focus
yourself and align yourself

00:14:47.490 --> 00:14:49.596 align:middle line:90%
with the day that's yet to come.

00:14:49.596 --> 00:14:50.410 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:14:50.410 --> 00:14:52.592 align:middle line:84%
In order to do
this exercise, you

00:14:52.592 --> 00:14:53.800 align:middle line:90%
have to learn Breath of Fire.

00:14:53.800 --> 00:14:55.280 align:middle line:90%
It's a really simple breath.

00:14:55.280 --> 00:14:57.890 align:middle line:90%
I'll teach it to you right now.

00:14:57.890 --> 00:15:00.920 align:middle line:84%
The one caveat is, if you're
pregnant or menstruating,

00:15:00.920 --> 00:15:02.660 align:middle line:90%
please don't do Breath of Fire.

00:15:02.660 --> 00:15:04.980 align:middle line:84%
Do ego eradicator,
this exercise,

00:15:04.980 --> 00:15:08.310 align:middle line:84%
with long, deep
breathing instead.

00:15:08.310 --> 00:15:12.050 align:middle line:84%
OK, to do Breath of Fire,
we emphasize the exhale.

00:15:12.050 --> 00:15:14.250 align:middle line:90%
And the inhale is passive.

00:15:14.250 --> 00:15:16.450 align:middle line:84%
When we exhale through
the nose rapidly,

00:15:16.450 --> 00:15:17.860 align:middle line:90%
we pull our navel point in.

00:15:17.860 --> 00:15:30.960 align:middle line:90%


00:15:30.960 --> 00:15:31.950 align:middle line:90%
Just like that.

00:15:31.950 --> 00:15:35.080 align:middle line:84%
So the inhale, it just
happens automatically.

00:15:35.080 --> 00:15:36.565 align:middle line:84%
The exhale, however,
is emphasized;

00:15:36.565 --> 00:15:39.900 align:middle line:84%
we're really moving the
air through the nostrils

00:15:39.900 --> 00:15:42.130 align:middle line:84%
rapidly as we pull
the navel point in.

00:15:42.130 --> 00:15:45.250 align:middle line:84%
OK, we're going to
add the arms to this.

00:15:45.250 --> 00:15:49.060 align:middle line:84%
So come up sitting
nice and tall.

00:15:49.060 --> 00:15:52.470 align:middle line:90%
Bring the arms up to 60 degrees.

00:15:52.470 --> 00:15:54.390 align:middle line:84%
Keep the arms
perfectly straight.

00:15:54.390 --> 00:15:56.720 align:middle line:90%
We'll close our eyes now.

00:15:56.720 --> 00:15:59.470 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going to focus my eyes
right here in between the two

00:15:59.470 --> 00:16:01.190 align:middle line:90%
eyebrows.

00:16:01.190 --> 00:16:03.750 align:middle line:90%
Take a deep inhale.

00:16:03.750 --> 00:16:05.210 align:middle line:90%
And let's begin Breath of Fire.

00:16:05.210 --> 00:16:31.760 align:middle line:90%


00:16:31.760 --> 00:16:32.895 align:middle line:90%
So take a deep inhale.

00:16:32.895 --> 00:16:35.690 align:middle line:90%


00:16:35.690 --> 00:16:40.110 align:middle line:84%
Touch the thumbs together
over the head, and exhale.

00:16:40.110 --> 00:16:42.920 align:middle line:90%


00:16:42.920 --> 00:16:44.820 align:middle line:90%
And relax.

00:16:44.820 --> 00:16:47.990 align:middle line:84%
So we did that for about
30 seconds to a minute.

00:16:47.990 --> 00:16:51.970 align:middle line:84%
Imagine three minutes a day
when you wake up each morning.

00:16:51.970 --> 00:16:54.560 align:middle line:84%
It'll give you inner
calm, strength,

00:16:54.560 --> 00:16:57.200 align:middle line:84%
and it's a tool you can use
to get control of your mind

00:16:57.200 --> 00:16:59.390 align:middle line:90%
before it gets control of you.

00:16:59.390 --> 00:17:00.850 align:middle line:90%
I wish that for you.

00:17:00.850 --> 00:17:02.072 align:middle line:90%
Have a great day.

00:17:02.072 --> 00:17:03.440 align:middle line:90%
[END PLAYBACK]

00:17:03.440 --> 00:17:05.819 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Where did you
learn that breath exercise?

00:17:05.819 --> 00:17:07.210 align:middle line:90%
That was very powerful.

00:17:07.210 --> 00:17:10.339 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: The ego
eradicator exercise

00:17:10.339 --> 00:17:13.314 align:middle line:84%
comes from the
kundalini yoga tradition

00:17:13.314 --> 00:17:15.359 align:middle line:90%
as taught by Yogi Bhajan.

00:17:15.359 --> 00:17:19.315 align:middle line:84%
So Yogi Bhajan brought that
one, and it brings together

00:17:19.315 --> 00:17:20.690 align:middle line:84%
a couple pretty
powerful element.

00:17:20.690 --> 00:17:22.369 align:middle line:84%
So you're working
with Breath of Fire,

00:17:22.369 --> 00:17:27.010 align:middle line:84%
which is a very powerful
breath, very detoxifying, very

00:17:27.010 --> 00:17:30.850 align:middle line:84%
energizing, focusing, very
powerful breath, increases

00:17:30.850 --> 00:17:33.465 align:middle line:84%
the lung capacity,
does a lot for you.

00:17:33.465 --> 00:17:34.840 align:middle line:84%
You're also working
with the arms

00:17:34.840 --> 00:17:37.080 align:middle line:84%
at a certain angle,
at 60 degrees.

00:17:37.080 --> 00:17:39.470 align:middle line:84%
So you're being asked
to keep your arms up

00:17:39.470 --> 00:17:42.690 align:middle line:84%
for a long period of time,
maybe three minutes or more.

00:17:42.690 --> 00:17:45.370 align:middle line:84%
And at some point in that
three minutes, your shoulders

00:17:45.370 --> 00:17:45.912 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Burn.

00:17:45.912 --> 00:17:47.203 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSEN: They're going to burn.

00:17:47.203 --> 00:17:49.100 align:middle line:84%
There's going to be a
conversation going on.

00:17:49.100 --> 00:17:51.290 align:middle line:84%
And the shoulders--
the mind will pipe in,

00:17:51.290 --> 00:17:54.690 align:middle line:84%
and the mind will say, you
know, please put your arms down.

00:17:54.690 --> 00:17:56.340 align:middle line:84%
Would you please
lower your arms?

00:17:56.340 --> 00:17:58.360 align:middle line:90%
Well, that's quite enough now.

00:17:58.360 --> 00:18:01.050 align:middle line:84%
No, seriously, put
your arms down.

00:18:01.050 --> 00:18:03.490 align:middle line:84%
And the conversation will
get more and more intense.

00:18:03.490 --> 00:18:08.300 align:middle line:84%
At a certain point, you stay
committed to the exercise.

00:18:08.300 --> 00:18:11.480 align:middle line:84%
You're digging deeper than
the muscles of the body.

00:18:11.480 --> 00:18:14.150 align:middle line:84%
Yes, you need your muscles
to hold your arms up,

00:18:14.150 --> 00:18:16.300 align:middle line:84%
but there's something
else going on.

00:18:16.300 --> 00:18:17.830 align:middle line:90%
What controls the muscles?

00:18:17.830 --> 00:18:19.890 align:middle line:84%
It's actually your
nervous system.

00:18:19.890 --> 00:18:21.550 align:middle line:84%
So the brain sends
an impulse down

00:18:21.550 --> 00:18:23.800 align:middle line:84%
through the central nervous
system, through the spine,

00:18:23.800 --> 00:18:26.850 align:middle line:84%
spinal cord, goes out to the
peripheral nervous system.

00:18:26.850 --> 00:18:28.870 align:middle line:84%
And it causes you
to use your muscles

00:18:28.870 --> 00:18:33.040 align:middle line:84%
to keep your arms
straight at 60 degrees.

00:18:33.040 --> 00:18:36.440 align:middle line:84%
The mind is presenting
a constant temptation.

00:18:36.440 --> 00:18:39.110 align:middle line:84%
The temptation is
lower the arms.

00:18:39.110 --> 00:18:40.610 align:middle line:84%
So what you're
actually doing is you

00:18:40.610 --> 00:18:44.820 align:middle line:84%
are facing a temptation, minute
to minute, breath by breath,

00:18:44.820 --> 00:18:46.430 align:middle line:84%
and you're resisting
the temptation.

00:18:46.430 --> 00:18:47.221 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Overriding.

00:18:47.221 --> 00:18:50.890 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: Overriding, making
your nervous system stronger.

00:18:50.890 --> 00:18:52.640 align:middle line:84%
You're actually tuning
your nervous system

00:18:52.640 --> 00:18:55.099 align:middle line:84%
to be able to resist
the temptation.

00:18:55.099 --> 00:18:56.640 align:middle line:84%
Now, when you get
out into the world,

00:18:56.640 --> 00:18:58.754 align:middle line:84%
there's all kinds
of temptations.

00:18:58.754 --> 00:19:00.420 align:middle line:84%
If we're going to
talk about addictions,

00:19:00.420 --> 00:19:02.330 align:middle line:84%
well, they're
everywhere all the time.

00:19:02.330 --> 00:19:03.970 align:middle line:84%
But maybe you're
trying to lose weight,

00:19:03.970 --> 00:19:06.290 align:middle line:84%
and you struggle with
a chocolate cake.

00:19:06.290 --> 00:19:09.579 align:middle line:84%
You come across a deli
window, and lo and behold,

00:19:09.579 --> 00:19:11.870 align:middle line:84%
there in the window is this
gorgeous piece of chocolate

00:19:11.870 --> 00:19:12.020 align:middle line:90%
cake.

00:19:12.020 --> 00:19:13.040 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you're
having a bad day.

00:19:13.040 --> 00:19:14.420 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSEN: Having a rough day.

00:19:14.420 --> 00:19:16.503 align:middle line:84%
Maybe you just had a bad
conversation with someone

00:19:16.503 --> 00:19:17.690 align:middle line:90%
you love or whatever it is.

00:19:17.690 --> 00:19:19.670 align:middle line:84%
And boy, that icing is
starting to look good.

00:19:19.670 --> 00:19:22.310 align:middle line:84%
And remember the first
time you had that cake?

00:19:22.310 --> 00:19:25.010 align:middle line:84%
And your mind starts
going down that road.

00:19:25.010 --> 00:19:27.950 align:middle line:84%
So now, you're in that
realm of temptation.

00:19:27.950 --> 00:19:31.740 align:middle line:84%
And so you are either going
to resist the temptation

00:19:31.740 --> 00:19:34.260 align:middle line:84%
and allow it to
pass and move on,

00:19:34.260 --> 00:19:35.960 align:middle line:84%
or you'll succumb
to the temptation,

00:19:35.960 --> 00:19:37.560 align:middle line:84%
and you'll have
the chocolate cake.

00:19:37.560 --> 00:19:42.290 align:middle line:84%
Now, just by practicing
strengthening your resolve

00:19:42.290 --> 00:19:44.800 align:middle line:84%
in the face of
temptation, represented

00:19:44.800 --> 00:19:47.240 align:middle line:84%
by keeping your arms
up when it's difficult,

00:19:47.240 --> 00:19:49.020 align:middle line:84%
you are increasing
the likelihood

00:19:49.020 --> 00:19:51.810 align:middle line:84%
you'll be able to resist
the temptation later on out

00:19:51.810 --> 00:19:53.050 align:middle line:90%
in the world.

00:19:53.050 --> 00:19:54.970 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And now how
does the kundalini

00:19:54.970 --> 00:19:56.970 align:middle line:90%
come into play with that?

00:19:56.970 --> 00:19:59.750 align:middle line:84%
Explain what that is
specifically, if you could.

00:19:59.750 --> 00:20:02.910 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: So the
kundalini energy is

00:20:02.910 --> 00:20:07.170 align:middle line:84%
thought to be the potential
energy of a human being which

00:20:07.170 --> 00:20:12.880 align:middle line:84%
exists and stays
locked, unaccessed,

00:20:12.880 --> 00:20:15.970 align:middle line:84%
at the base of the spine,
right in the sacrum,

00:20:15.970 --> 00:20:17.900 align:middle line:90%
right in the base of the spine.

00:20:17.900 --> 00:20:21.000 align:middle line:84%
And through these exercises,
we are tapping into

00:20:21.000 --> 00:20:24.790 align:middle line:84%
and releasing that energy,
distributing it around the body

00:20:24.790 --> 00:20:27.780 align:middle line:84%
so that we can become a fully
actualized and activated

00:20:27.780 --> 00:20:28.740 align:middle line:90%
individual.

00:20:28.740 --> 00:20:29.590 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Beautiful.

00:20:29.590 --> 00:20:31.390 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: That is a
beautiful concept.

00:20:31.390 --> 00:20:33.830 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes, that's a bit
above someone else's head.

00:20:33.830 --> 00:20:35.663 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: No, that was a
beautiful definition.

00:20:35.663 --> 00:20:36.600 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSEN: OK.

00:20:36.600 --> 00:20:38.490 align:middle line:84%
I would just simply
say to people,

00:20:38.490 --> 00:20:42.020 align:middle line:84%
you know, we all
know somebody that

00:20:42.020 --> 00:20:44.570 align:middle line:90%
is completely in their power.

00:20:44.570 --> 00:20:50.710 align:middle line:84%
And you see them, and you think,
my god, they're just on point.

00:20:50.710 --> 00:20:53.250 align:middle line:84%
They're just doing what
they're supposed to be doing.

00:20:53.250 --> 00:20:57.850 align:middle line:84%
It looks and it feels just
like they're right on mission.

00:20:57.850 --> 00:20:59.670 align:middle line:90%
They're activated.

00:20:59.670 --> 00:21:02.140 align:middle line:84%
Somehow, they've tapped
into that energy.

00:21:02.140 --> 00:21:04.240 align:middle line:84%
Maybe they've practice
kundalini yoga.

00:21:04.240 --> 00:21:06.520 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it got
activated another way.

00:21:06.520 --> 00:21:10.690 align:middle line:84%
But they are-- they've dug
into their personal self,

00:21:10.690 --> 00:21:13.300 align:middle line:84%
and they're able to
create from that place.

00:21:13.300 --> 00:21:15.080 align:middle line:90%
Amazing to be around them.

00:21:15.080 --> 00:21:15.940 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:21:15.940 --> 00:21:17.796 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: These exercises
really help us.

00:21:17.796 --> 00:21:19.170 align:middle line:84%
And when you've
been so off track

00:21:19.170 --> 00:21:22.190 align:middle line:84%
to be caught in addiction,
to be able to come back home

00:21:22.190 --> 00:21:26.640 align:middle line:84%
to the home office, which is the
heart, that is very powerful.

00:21:26.640 --> 00:21:28.350 align:middle line:84%
These practices
really help with that.

00:21:28.350 --> 00:21:29.808 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: There is
a video here where

00:21:29.808 --> 00:21:33.061 align:middle line:84%
Tommy's talking about how he
got in touch with kundalini.

00:21:33.061 --> 00:21:33.560 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

