00:21:38.917 --> 00:21:42.740 align:middle line:84%
-People sometimes ask me,
why build a yoga and recovery

00:21:42.740 --> 00:21:43.520 align:middle line:90%
program?

00:21:43.520 --> 00:21:44.410 align:middle line:90%
What is the benefit?

00:21:44.410 --> 00:21:46.290 align:middle line:90%
Why do this?

00:21:46.290 --> 00:21:50.150 align:middle line:84%
And what I tell them is when
I turned 20 years sober,

00:21:50.150 --> 00:21:52.580 align:middle line:84%
I went to pick up
my 20 year chip.

00:21:52.580 --> 00:21:55.370 align:middle line:84%
The guy who handed me that
chip had, congratulations!

00:21:55.370 --> 00:21:57.950 align:middle line:90%
You're 1 in 1,000.

00:21:57.950 --> 00:22:01.660 align:middle line:84%
I thought to myself,
like, how grim is that?

00:22:01.660 --> 00:22:05.090 align:middle line:84%
999 people aren't
going to make it,

00:22:05.090 --> 00:22:07.450 align:middle line:84%
and one person makes it
to long term sobriety.

00:22:07.450 --> 00:22:09.960 align:middle line:84%
That's what he was
essentially saying.

00:22:09.960 --> 00:22:13.070 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, my god,
there's a better way.

00:22:13.070 --> 00:22:16.015 align:middle line:84%
There has to be a way to
improve those odds for people

00:22:16.015 --> 00:22:17.890 align:middle line:84%
out there who are trying
to-- not just trying

00:22:17.890 --> 00:22:21.340 align:middle line:84%
to get into recovery, but
people who've been in recovery.

00:22:21.340 --> 00:22:22.987 align:middle line:90%
How do you stay on that path?

00:22:22.987 --> 00:22:25.070 align:middle line:84%
I consider myself one of
the most fortunate people

00:22:25.070 --> 00:22:26.370 align:middle line:90%
in the world.

00:22:26.370 --> 00:22:30.920 align:middle line:84%
I was able to find the
amazing program, the 12 steps,

00:22:30.920 --> 00:22:32.960 align:middle line:90%
and to overcome acute addiction.

00:22:32.960 --> 00:22:37.490 align:middle line:84%
What I did not find were ways
that I could more effectively

00:22:37.490 --> 00:22:41.580 align:middle line:84%
live my life and get over
some of the other kinds

00:22:41.580 --> 00:22:44.660 align:middle line:84%
of addictions that I
was still dealing with.

00:22:44.660 --> 00:22:47.820 align:middle line:84%
I still was living in
the energy of addiction

00:22:47.820 --> 00:22:49.460 align:middle line:90%
even in my recovery.

00:22:49.460 --> 00:22:51.320 align:middle line:84%
How do I get beyond
the energy of addiction

00:22:51.320 --> 00:22:53.870 align:middle line:84%
to what I would
call true recovery?

00:22:53.870 --> 00:22:56.600 align:middle line:84%
And the answer came for me
through the path of yoga.

00:22:56.600 --> 00:23:00.490 align:middle line:84%
Yoga helps you
build the capacity

00:23:00.490 --> 00:23:03.750 align:middle line:84%
to move the issues
out of your tissues.

00:23:03.750 --> 00:23:08.230 align:middle line:84%
Stuck emotional energy
and trauma in the body

00:23:08.230 --> 00:23:11.190 align:middle line:90%
keeps you stuck in the past.

00:23:11.190 --> 00:23:14.950 align:middle line:84%
Yoga moves those energies
through and liberates you

00:23:14.950 --> 00:23:17.840 align:middle line:90%
so you can become fully present.

00:23:17.840 --> 00:23:22.000 align:middle line:84%
And all those years of
recovery, which were amazing,

00:23:22.000 --> 00:23:25.300 align:middle line:84%
and I was overcoming
acute drug addiction,

00:23:25.300 --> 00:23:27.790 align:middle line:90%
those were wonderful years.

00:23:27.790 --> 00:23:29.270 align:middle line:90%
But I needed something more.

00:23:29.270 --> 00:23:30.270 align:middle line:90%
And I found it.

00:23:30.270 --> 00:23:32.920 align:middle line:84%
There are practices
that exist that

00:23:32.920 --> 00:23:34.990 align:middle line:84%
will make your
recovery stronger,

00:23:34.990 --> 00:23:38.140 align:middle line:84%
that will stack the
odds more in your favor

00:23:38.140 --> 00:23:43.270 align:middle line:84%
to stay on that path, that will
prevent relapse from happening,

00:23:43.270 --> 00:23:45.660 align:middle line:84%
and that will help you to
build a fulfilling, sweet life.

00:23:45.660 --> 00:23:52.560 align:middle line:90%


00:23:52.560 --> 00:23:56.670 align:middle line:84%
My recovery in the 12
steps took me to the point

00:23:56.670 --> 00:24:00.250 align:middle line:84%
where I overcame
acute addiction.

00:24:00.250 --> 00:24:03.140 align:middle line:84%
But I was still swimming
in the energy of addiction

00:24:03.140 --> 00:24:05.630 align:middle line:90%
in other ways in my life.

00:24:05.630 --> 00:24:08.050 align:middle line:84%
And it was no longer
acceptable to me.

00:24:08.050 --> 00:24:11.920 align:middle line:84%
And the way the universe
made that clear to me was it

00:24:11.920 --> 00:24:14.750 align:middle line:90%
took away my ability to move.

00:24:14.750 --> 00:24:17.320 align:middle line:84%
I developed a debilitating
back condition.

00:24:17.320 --> 00:24:20.170 align:middle line:84%
I could no longer
walk without pain.

00:24:20.170 --> 00:24:21.970 align:middle line:84%
It got worse and
worse and worse.

00:24:21.970 --> 00:24:24.000 align:middle line:84%
I tried everything I
could to get over it.

00:24:24.000 --> 00:24:27.830 align:middle line:84%
More yoga, no yoga,
trainers, massage therapists,

00:24:27.830 --> 00:24:33.400 align:middle line:84%
chiropractors, anything
I could get my hands on.

00:24:33.400 --> 00:24:34.582 align:middle line:90%
And I was still sick.

00:24:34.582 --> 00:24:36.290 align:middle line:84%
I started to feel like
maybe this was it.

00:24:36.290 --> 00:24:38.660 align:middle line:84%
Like at 35 years old,
I was just not going

00:24:38.660 --> 00:24:41.080 align:middle line:84%
to be able to walk and
move freely anymore.

00:24:41.080 --> 00:24:43.610 align:middle line:84%
It was a very
frightening time for me.

00:24:43.610 --> 00:24:46.910 align:middle line:84%
So one day, a friend
comes to me and says,

00:24:46.910 --> 00:24:49.680 align:middle line:84%
look, if you really
want to heal your back,

00:24:49.680 --> 00:24:52.292 align:middle line:84%
you need to go see this
guy named Guru Prem.

00:24:52.292 --> 00:24:55.230 align:middle line:84%
And I'm thinking
Guru Prem, Guru Prem.

00:24:55.230 --> 00:24:57.940 align:middle line:84%
No, I'm not going
to go see some guru.

00:24:57.940 --> 00:24:59.662 align:middle line:84%
Like, I've been through
all these people.

00:24:59.662 --> 00:25:00.370 align:middle line:90%
All these things.

00:25:00.370 --> 00:25:01.680 align:middle line:90%
I'm trying, trying everything.

00:25:01.680 --> 00:25:03.050 align:middle line:90%
But I'm not going to some guru.

00:25:03.050 --> 00:25:05.610 align:middle line:84%
I can see the
turban and the beard

00:25:05.610 --> 00:25:09.770 align:middle line:84%
and the robes, the whole thing,
and it's just not for me.

00:25:09.770 --> 00:25:12.940 align:middle line:84%
So my friend says,
OK, that's fine.

00:25:12.940 --> 00:25:15.181 align:middle line:84%
Well, that night I went
out to dinner with my wife.

00:25:15.181 --> 00:25:17.180 align:middle line:84%
And there was a woman at
the table next to ours.

00:25:17.180 --> 00:25:20.330 align:middle line:90%
And we struck up a conversation.

00:25:20.330 --> 00:25:21.830 align:middle line:84%
She had just moved
to Los Angeles.

00:25:21.830 --> 00:25:25.200 align:middle line:84%
And we asked why,
what brings you here?

00:25:25.200 --> 00:25:26.900 align:middle line:84%
She says, oh, I came
here really to see

00:25:26.900 --> 00:25:30.000 align:middle line:90%
this man named Guru Prem.

00:25:30.000 --> 00:25:32.440 align:middle line:84%
So you see, my life has been
a series of second chances

00:25:32.440 --> 00:25:33.410 align:middle line:90%
like this.

00:25:33.410 --> 00:25:36.970 align:middle line:84%
Despite myself, I got
the pretty clear message

00:25:36.970 --> 00:25:39.560 align:middle line:84%
that I was supposed to see
this guy named Guru Prem.

00:25:39.560 --> 00:25:42.270 align:middle line:84%
I called him the next morning
and I said, apparently,

00:25:42.270 --> 00:25:43.900 align:middle line:90%
I'm supposed to come see you.

00:25:43.900 --> 00:25:47.520 align:middle line:84%
And he said, well, you
better get in here then.

00:25:47.520 --> 00:25:51.270 align:middle line:84%
For the next five years, I
sat opposite him once a week.

00:25:51.270 --> 00:25:53.450 align:middle line:90%
He taught me how to breathe.

00:25:53.450 --> 00:25:55.690 align:middle line:90%
He taught me how to move.

00:25:55.690 --> 00:25:59.790 align:middle line:84%
He taught me how to
interact with people.

00:25:59.790 --> 00:26:02.970 align:middle line:84%
He taught me about
relationships with women.

00:26:02.970 --> 00:26:07.420 align:middle line:84%
He gave me a parameter
for living my life

00:26:07.420 --> 00:26:10.230 align:middle line:90%
in a way that made sense to me.

00:26:10.230 --> 00:26:14.430 align:middle line:84%
Essentially, he gave
me things to aspire to.

00:26:14.430 --> 00:26:17.350 align:middle line:90%
And he taught me kundalini yoga.

00:26:17.350 --> 00:26:20.660 align:middle line:84%
And in three months, I
was able to heal my back.

00:26:20.660 --> 00:26:23.250 align:middle line:84%
I had been told
by the top doctors

00:26:23.250 --> 00:26:27.540 align:middle line:84%
here that it was manage your
pain for the rest of your life,

00:26:27.540 --> 00:26:30.150 align:middle line:84%
and eventually we'll
look to surgery.

00:26:30.150 --> 00:26:34.660 align:middle line:84%
And thank god that was not the
fate that ended up unfolding

00:26:34.660 --> 00:26:35.520 align:middle line:90%
for me.

