00:48:12.760 --> 00:48:14.490 align:middle line:84%
-How do we measure
success in recovery?

00:48:14.490 --> 00:48:17.170 align:middle line:90%


00:48:17.170 --> 00:48:20.080 align:middle line:90%
Is success a metric?

00:48:20.080 --> 00:48:21.892 align:middle line:90%
Oh, I stayed sober for a year.

00:48:21.892 --> 00:48:24.100 align:middle line:84%
Nevermind the fact that I
was miserable for the year,

00:48:24.100 --> 00:48:24.960 align:middle line:90%
but I stayed sober.

00:48:24.960 --> 00:48:26.670 align:middle line:90%
Isn't that a success?

00:48:26.670 --> 00:48:27.620 align:middle line:90%
No!

00:48:27.620 --> 00:48:30.100 align:middle line:90%
That's not a success to me.

00:48:30.100 --> 00:48:32.630 align:middle line:84%
Success is measured
on the inside.

00:48:32.630 --> 00:48:35.720 align:middle line:84%
How do we create
profound transformation

00:48:35.720 --> 00:48:37.570 align:middle line:90%
within a human being?

00:48:37.570 --> 00:48:39.100 align:middle line:84%
So that a person
who used to think

00:48:39.100 --> 00:48:41.540 align:middle line:84%
about drugs and alcohol or
some other addictive behavior

00:48:41.540 --> 00:48:45.450 align:middle line:84%
all the time no longer
thinks about those behaviors,

00:48:45.450 --> 00:48:48.130 align:middle line:84%
and now actually is more
concerned about the well-being

00:48:48.130 --> 00:48:52.474 align:middle line:84%
of family and community,
maybe about manifesting dreams

00:48:52.474 --> 00:48:54.140 align:middle line:84%
and helping other
people to do the same?

00:48:54.140 --> 00:48:56.890 align:middle line:90%


00:48:56.890 --> 00:48:59.920 align:middle line:84%
How do we create a
success if we don't even

00:48:59.920 --> 00:49:01.030 align:middle line:90%
know what it looks like?

00:49:01.030 --> 00:49:03.810 align:middle line:90%


00:49:03.810 --> 00:49:05.276 align:middle line:84%
If we're always in
12 step meetings

00:49:05.276 --> 00:49:07.400 align:middle line:84%
and we're always raising
our hand, I'm Tommy,

00:49:07.400 --> 00:49:11.220 align:middle line:84%
I'm an addict, that puts a
mixed signal out into the world,

00:49:11.220 --> 00:49:12.580 align:middle line:90%
doesn't it?

00:49:12.580 --> 00:49:14.819 align:middle line:90%
I'm 23 years in recovery.

00:49:14.819 --> 00:49:16.860 align:middle line:84%
If I'm saying to a person
who doesn't understand,

00:49:16.860 --> 00:49:19.220 align:middle line:84%
I'm an addict, I'm an
alcoholic, doesn't that

00:49:19.220 --> 00:49:22.620 align:middle line:84%
send a signal to them that
I don't think I'm well?

00:49:22.620 --> 00:49:25.960 align:middle line:84%
That I haven't yet
gotten past this thing?

00:49:25.960 --> 00:49:28.160 align:middle line:90%
When do you recover?

00:49:28.160 --> 00:49:30.545 align:middle line:90%
How does a success look?

00:49:30.545 --> 00:49:33.070 align:middle line:90%


00:49:33.070 --> 00:49:37.360 align:middle line:84%
Well, addiction of
all kinds doesn't

00:49:37.360 --> 00:49:40.370 align:middle line:90%
look like you think it looks.

00:49:40.370 --> 00:49:41.870 align:middle line:90%
It looks like me.

00:49:41.870 --> 00:49:42.850 align:middle line:90%
It looks like him.

00:49:42.850 --> 00:49:44.020 align:middle line:90%
It looks like her.

00:49:44.020 --> 00:49:47.420 align:middle line:84%
It looks like people at every
economic level in our society,

00:49:47.420 --> 00:49:50.035 align:middle line:84%
people of every
race, creed, gender.

00:49:50.035 --> 00:49:53.970 align:middle line:90%


00:49:53.970 --> 00:49:56.230 align:middle line:84%
If we don't come out
and tell our story,

00:49:56.230 --> 00:50:00.330 align:middle line:84%
if we don't share with the
world what a success looks like,

00:50:00.330 --> 00:50:04.600 align:middle line:84%
why would anybody except a
desperate person, broken down,

00:50:04.600 --> 00:50:08.740 align:middle line:84%
ever want to be attracted
into a 12 step room?

00:50:08.740 --> 00:50:11.270 align:middle line:90%
Is it a party going on in there?

00:50:11.270 --> 00:50:14.070 align:middle line:84%
Well, actually, it is a
party going on in there,

00:50:14.070 --> 00:50:19.940 align:middle line:84%
but you wouldn't know it because
unless you're a desperate, fall

00:50:19.940 --> 00:50:22.660 align:middle line:84%
down drunk, I had
nowhere else to turn,

00:50:22.660 --> 00:50:26.740 align:middle line:84%
so I turned to the 12 steps--
unless you were that desperate,

00:50:26.740 --> 00:50:28.190 align:middle line:90%
you wouldn't end up there.

00:50:28.190 --> 00:50:31.230 align:middle line:84%
Unless a court sent you there,
you wouldn't end up there.

00:50:31.230 --> 00:50:34.210 align:middle line:84%
Unless your family left you,
you wouldn't end up there.

00:50:34.210 --> 00:50:37.470 align:middle line:84%
Because you don't know what
a success looks like that's

00:50:37.470 --> 00:50:40.380 align:middle line:90%
come out of those rooms.

00:50:40.380 --> 00:50:44.210 align:middle line:84%
People get on my case from 12
step programs all the time.

00:50:44.210 --> 00:50:45.280 align:middle line:90%
And don't get me wrong.

00:50:45.280 --> 00:50:46.320 align:middle line:90%
I love the 12 steps.

00:50:46.320 --> 00:50:47.490 align:middle line:90%
They saved my life.

00:50:47.490 --> 00:50:50.489 align:middle line:90%
And I love most of its members.

00:50:50.489 --> 00:50:52.530 align:middle line:84%
Most of the people who
follow that path, I really

00:50:52.530 --> 00:50:55.250 align:middle line:84%
appreciate the idea that these
people are going to live along

00:50:55.250 --> 00:50:57.760 align:middle line:84%
a spiritual path,
work at being honest,

00:50:57.760 --> 00:50:59.320 align:middle line:90%
try to clean up their mistakes.

00:50:59.320 --> 00:51:00.620 align:middle line:90%
I love all those things.

00:51:00.620 --> 00:51:03.760 align:middle line:84%
It's a wonderful,
wonderful program.

00:51:03.760 --> 00:51:05.379 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people give
me crap, though.

00:51:05.379 --> 00:51:06.920 align:middle line:84%
And they're like,
you're not supposed

00:51:06.920 --> 00:51:09.790 align:middle line:84%
to go out and speak
about these things!

00:51:09.790 --> 00:51:13.350 align:middle line:84%
You're not supposed to go out
and represent a fellowship.

00:51:13.350 --> 00:51:15.460 align:middle line:84%
And I just tell them what
I tell you right now.

00:51:15.460 --> 00:51:17.780 align:middle line:84%
I'm not representing
a fellowship.

00:51:17.780 --> 00:51:19.960 align:middle line:84%
I'm not representing
any fellowship.

00:51:19.960 --> 00:51:22.310 align:middle line:84%
I'm not a member
of a fellowship.

00:51:22.310 --> 00:51:26.370 align:middle line:84%
I'm a human being, and I walk
the path of the 12 steps.

00:51:26.370 --> 00:51:29.490 align:middle line:84%
And it saved my life from
acute drug addiction.

00:51:29.490 --> 00:51:31.290 align:middle line:84%
And the path of
yoga and meditation

00:51:31.290 --> 00:51:33.410 align:middle line:84%
and healthy, conscious
lifestyle choices

00:51:33.410 --> 00:51:35.660 align:middle line:90%
took me the rest of the way.

00:51:35.660 --> 00:51:38.820 align:middle line:84%
Now, I do in my life
just what that guy who

00:51:38.820 --> 00:51:41.450 align:middle line:84%
had that spiritual
awakening back in 1935,

00:51:41.450 --> 00:51:43.230 align:middle line:90%
just what he figured out.

00:51:43.230 --> 00:51:46.090 align:middle line:84%
Now, I pass it on to
another human being.

00:51:46.090 --> 00:51:48.310 align:middle line:84%
But I don't do it
from within the guise

00:51:48.310 --> 00:51:52.460 align:middle line:84%
of I'm a broken person,
or I'm still an addict,

00:51:52.460 --> 00:51:55.540 align:middle line:90%
or I'm still suffering.

00:51:55.540 --> 00:51:56.040 align:middle line:90%
No, no no.

00:51:56.040 --> 00:51:57.680 align:middle line:90%
I just do it as a human being.

00:51:57.680 --> 00:51:59.230 align:middle line:90%
That means I have joy.

00:51:59.230 --> 00:52:00.900 align:middle line:90%
I have challenges.

00:52:00.900 --> 00:52:02.730 align:middle line:90%
I suffer and grieve.

00:52:02.730 --> 00:52:04.430 align:middle line:90%
I get better and well.

00:52:04.430 --> 00:52:05.560 align:middle line:90%
I have fun.

00:52:05.560 --> 00:52:08.210 align:middle line:84%
I have a complete and
full and wonderful life.

00:52:08.210 --> 00:52:10.387 align:middle line:84%
And from that place,
I'm truly able to help

00:52:10.387 --> 00:52:11.220 align:middle line:90%
another human being.

00:52:11.220 --> 00:52:11.980 align:middle line:90%
[END PLAYBACK]

00:52:11.980 --> 00:52:14.960 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you don't
agree with that language

00:52:14.960 --> 00:52:20.380 align:middle line:84%
of once an addict, I am an
addict languaging, do you?

00:52:20.380 --> 00:52:24.790 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: No, that's
problematic for me as a yogi

00:52:24.790 --> 00:52:26.250 align:middle line:90%
and as a human being.

00:52:26.250 --> 00:52:29.660 align:middle line:84%
So what we-- I want
to be very clear here.

00:52:29.660 --> 00:52:34.740 align:middle line:84%
I love the 12 step program, very
helpful to me, saved my life.

00:52:34.740 --> 00:52:35.440 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Totally.

00:52:35.440 --> 00:52:37.740 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: So this is not
bashing that society

00:52:37.740 --> 00:52:38.780 align:middle line:90%
or bashing that program.

00:52:38.780 --> 00:52:39.654 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Please, yeah.

00:52:39.654 --> 00:52:42.830 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: It's simply saying
that the 12 steps are

00:52:42.830 --> 00:52:45.490 align:middle line:84%
too effective to overlook, but
they're not effective enough

00:52:45.490 --> 00:52:48.520 align:middle line:84%
to say that they're perfect
and beyond improvement.

00:52:48.520 --> 00:52:50.040 align:middle line:84%
That the way people
approach them

00:52:50.040 --> 00:52:53.720 align:middle line:84%
in this society that's around
them should be always looking

00:52:53.720 --> 00:52:56.280 align:middle line:84%
to figure out how can
it do things better?

00:52:56.280 --> 00:52:58.980 align:middle line:84%
One of the off-putting
things about that society,

00:52:58.980 --> 00:53:01.610 align:middle line:84%
I think, to many people
that I've spoken with

00:53:01.610 --> 00:53:04.530 align:middle line:84%
is that they don't
understand why-- so I'm

00:53:04.530 --> 00:53:07.270 align:middle line:90%
23 years sober, right?

00:53:07.270 --> 00:53:09.920 align:middle line:84%
I haven't had a drink
or a drug for 23 years.

00:53:09.920 --> 00:53:12.110 align:middle line:84%
You would think, as
a casual onlooker,

00:53:12.110 --> 00:53:16.920 align:middle line:84%
you think, well, you
must be better now.

00:53:16.920 --> 00:53:17.850 align:middle line:90%
You must be cured.

00:53:17.850 --> 00:53:19.476 align:middle line:84%
But if I raise my
hand in front of you,

00:53:19.476 --> 00:53:20.516 align:middle line:90%
and you don't understand.

00:53:20.516 --> 00:53:22.155 align:middle line:84%
I say, my name is
Tommy, I'm an addict.

00:53:22.155 --> 00:53:25.110 align:middle line:84%
You say, well, I
don't understand.

00:53:25.110 --> 00:53:26.875 align:middle line:84%
When do you get better
from this thing?

00:53:26.875 --> 00:53:27.458 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:53:27.458 --> 00:53:29.850 align:middle line:84%
So what would you raise
your hand and say instead?

00:53:29.850 --> 00:53:30.950 align:middle line:90%
My name is Tommy--

00:53:30.950 --> 00:53:33.110 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: I'm in
recovery from addiction.

00:53:33.110 --> 00:53:36.430 align:middle line:84%
Or I'm a person in
long term recovery.

00:53:36.430 --> 00:53:39.730 align:middle line:90%
Or I have experienced addiction.

00:53:39.730 --> 00:53:43.570 align:middle line:84%
Or I've recovered from drug
addiction and alcoholism.

00:53:43.570 --> 00:53:46.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Or I moved beyond.

00:53:46.060 --> 00:53:47.700 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: I've moved
beyond addiction.

00:53:47.700 --> 00:53:49.870 align:middle line:84%
That would really
raise some feathers.

00:53:49.870 --> 00:53:50.590 align:middle line:84%
That would really
raise some feathers.

00:53:50.590 --> 00:53:51.298 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Would it?

00:53:51.298 --> 00:53:54.030 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: Oh, that would be
a revolutionary statement.

00:53:54.030 --> 00:53:55.360 align:middle line:90%
I've moved beyond addiction.

00:53:55.360 --> 00:53:55.860 align:middle line:90%
You see?

00:53:55.860 --> 00:53:59.280 align:middle line:84%
Because most people in the field
don't believe that's possible.

00:53:59.280 --> 00:54:02.220 align:middle line:84%
Now, what I'm interested in
in your question earlier was,

00:54:02.220 --> 00:54:04.940 align:middle line:90%
how should we treat addicts?

00:54:04.940 --> 00:54:07.190 align:middle line:84%
We should treat
them with treatment.

00:54:07.190 --> 00:54:09.870 align:middle line:84%
We should treat them
with compassionate means

00:54:09.870 --> 00:54:13.280 align:middle line:84%
to help them get better
from a disease recognized

00:54:13.280 --> 00:54:15.970 align:middle line:84%
by the American Medical
Association that

00:54:15.970 --> 00:54:17.600 align:middle line:90%
has a treatment.

00:54:17.600 --> 00:54:20.360 align:middle line:84%
If you apply the
treatment, you get better.

00:54:20.360 --> 00:54:22.270 align:middle line:84%
Once you get better,
you need to start

00:54:22.270 --> 00:54:24.590 align:middle line:84%
thinking about
bringing lifestyle

00:54:24.590 --> 00:54:27.040 align:middle line:84%
elements into your life that
are going to make your body

00:54:27.040 --> 00:54:29.470 align:middle line:90%
and your mind work really well.

00:54:29.470 --> 00:54:31.510 align:middle line:84%
Keep moving forward
in your life.

00:54:31.510 --> 00:54:34.780 align:middle line:84%
But at some point, that I'm
Tommy and I'm an addict,

00:54:34.780 --> 00:54:36.860 align:middle line:90%
it has to change.

00:54:36.860 --> 00:54:40.330 align:middle line:84%
Because I truly believe we're
moving beyond addiction.

00:54:40.330 --> 00:54:42.460 align:middle line:84%
And if you don't
think it's possible,

00:54:42.460 --> 00:54:45.570 align:middle line:84%
you're not going to try
to go beyond addiction.

00:54:45.570 --> 00:54:48.840 align:middle line:84%
Someone would have to
tell you it's possible.

00:54:48.840 --> 00:54:50.860 align:middle line:90%
It's hard, but try.

00:54:50.860 --> 00:54:53.080 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Maybe it's the
first five years, two years

00:54:53.080 --> 00:54:53.700 align:middle line:90%
or whatever.

00:54:53.700 --> 00:54:55.080 align:middle line:90%
You say that.

00:54:55.080 --> 00:55:00.060 align:middle line:84%
And then, you start at the mile
marker, I've moved beyond--

00:55:00.060 --> 00:55:01.725 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSEN: Stages of recovery.

00:55:01.725 --> 00:55:05.397 align:middle line:84%
And it happens at different
times for different people.

00:55:05.397 --> 00:55:05.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I see.

00:55:05.980 --> 00:55:08.110 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSEN: People say, well,
now you're recovered.

00:55:08.110 --> 00:55:10.610 align:middle line:84%
Does that mean you can go out
and drink and it's no problem?

00:55:10.610 --> 00:55:11.110 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:55:11.110 --> 00:55:13.810 align:middle line:84%
It means I have no desire to do
something that would intoxicate

00:55:13.810 --> 00:55:16.029 align:middle line:90%
my mind, body, and spirit.

00:55:16.029 --> 00:55:16.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ever again.

00:55:16.820 --> 00:55:17.280 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSEN: I have no desire.

00:55:17.280 --> 00:55:18.830 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you're not
in resistance to it.

00:55:18.830 --> 00:55:20.413 align:middle line:84%
You just don't have
any desire for it.

00:55:20.413 --> 00:55:21.990 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSEN: Why would I do that?

00:55:21.990 --> 00:55:24.450 align:middle line:84%
I'm interested in
greater awareness,

00:55:24.450 --> 00:55:25.660 align:middle line:90%
greater consciousness.

00:55:25.660 --> 00:55:26.969 align:middle line:90%
That's what gets me jazzed.

00:55:26.969 --> 00:55:28.010 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's beautiful.

00:55:28.010 --> 00:55:28.940 align:middle line:90%
That's beautiful.

00:55:28.940 --> 00:55:30.606 align:middle line:84%
There's a whole piece
here where Tommy's

00:55:30.606 --> 00:55:31.790 align:middle line:90%
talking about moving beyond.

00:55:31.790 --> 00:55:32.673 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

00:55:32.673 --> 00:55:33.360 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:55:33.360 --> 00:55:36.650 align:middle line:84%
-So I guess the whole point
of this is just simply to say,

00:55:36.650 --> 00:55:39.550 align:middle line:84%
if we're really going to
move forward as a society,

00:55:39.550 --> 00:55:42.050 align:middle line:84%
we're going to have to start
to understand what works about

00:55:42.050 --> 00:55:45.330 align:middle line:90%
the 12 steps and what doesn't.

00:55:45.330 --> 00:55:48.990 align:middle line:84%
We can't throw it out as if it's
the baby with the bath water.

00:55:48.990 --> 00:55:54.300 align:middle line:84%
The 12 steps, there's such
magic and such power in there.

00:55:54.300 --> 00:55:58.020 align:middle line:84%
But the fact is it's
not a perfect program.

00:55:58.020 --> 00:56:01.530 align:middle line:84%
It's too effective
to be overlooked,

00:56:01.530 --> 00:56:05.565 align:middle line:84%
but it's not effective enough
to be beyond improvement.

00:56:05.565 --> 00:56:07.690 align:middle line:84%
So we're going to have to
take a deep look at that.

00:56:07.690 --> 00:56:09.620 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to have
to look at our policy.

00:56:09.620 --> 00:56:11.700 align:middle line:84%
How do we treat
addicts in our world?

00:56:11.700 --> 00:56:13.290 align:middle line:90%
Do we send them to prison?

00:56:13.290 --> 00:56:16.270 align:middle line:84%
It's basically a school for
becoming an addict, right?

00:56:16.270 --> 00:56:19.580 align:middle line:84%
Or are we going to help
them get treatment?

00:56:19.580 --> 00:56:22.180 align:middle line:84%
There's a lot of
room for improvement.

00:56:22.180 --> 00:56:25.370 align:middle line:84%
But we really have to
come together right now,

00:56:25.370 --> 00:56:28.184 align:middle line:84%
and we have to take a holistic
approach to this thing.

00:56:28.184 --> 00:56:29.850 align:middle line:84%
We have to understand
addiction goes way

00:56:29.850 --> 00:56:31.800 align:middle line:90%
beyond just drugs and alcohol.

00:56:31.800 --> 00:56:34.180 align:middle line:84%
And in our treatment
approaches, we

00:56:34.180 --> 00:56:36.040 align:middle line:84%
have to understand that
things like learning

00:56:36.040 --> 00:56:38.800 align:middle line:84%
how to breathe properly, like
in the yogic style of breathing

00:56:38.800 --> 00:56:41.750 align:middle line:84%
and meditation, are going
to be very important.

00:56:41.750 --> 00:56:43.490 align:middle line:84%
That treating our body
well, and actually

00:56:43.490 --> 00:56:46.666 align:middle line:84%
learning how to manage stress,
that's going to be important.

00:56:46.666 --> 00:56:48.540 align:middle line:84%
We're going to have to
learn that food is not

00:56:48.540 --> 00:56:50.050 align:middle line:90%
an outside issue.

00:56:50.050 --> 00:56:51.860 align:middle line:90%
Food is an inside issue.

00:56:51.860 --> 00:56:54.600 align:middle line:84%
And if we don't take a look
at our relationship to food,

00:56:54.600 --> 00:56:56.558 align:middle line:84%
there's going to be
something seriously missing

00:56:56.558 --> 00:56:58.304 align:middle line:90%
from our path of recovery.

00:56:58.304 --> 00:56:59.970 align:middle line:84%
We're going to have
to learn that things

00:56:59.970 --> 00:57:02.640 align:middle line:84%
like vocational
training, life coaching,

00:57:02.640 --> 00:57:05.160 align:middle line:84%
and actually learning what
our mission and our purpose

00:57:05.160 --> 00:57:07.830 align:middle line:84%
is on this planet, those
are important things.

